 {"content": "Task", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2101, "length": 4}}, {"content": "1.2", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2106, "length": 3}}, {"content": "will", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2110, "length": 4}}, {"content": "be", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2115, "length": 2}}, {"content": "used", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2118, "length": 4}}, {"content": "as", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2123, "length": 2}}, {"content": "control.", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2126, "length": 8}}, {"content": "NK", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2135, "length": 2}}, {"content": "and", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2138, "length": 3}}, {"content": "T", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2142, "length": 1}}, {"content": "cell", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2144, "length": 4}}, {"content": "activity", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2149, "length": 8}}, {"content": "and", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2158, "length": 3}}, {"content": "cytotoxicity", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2162, "length": 12}}, {"content": "levels", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2175, "length": 6}}, {"content": "will", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2182, "length": 4}}, {"content": "be", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2187, "length": 2}}, {"content": "measured", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2190, "length": 8}}, {"content": "as", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2199, "length": 2}}, {"content": "in", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2202, "length": 2}}, {"content": "Task", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2205, "length": 4}}, {"content": "1.2.", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 2210, "length": 4}}], "spans": [{"offset": 0, "length": 2235}]}], "tables": [{"rowCount": 4, "columnCount": 2, "cells": [{"rowIndex": 0, "columnIndex": 0, "content": "Work package number", "spans": [{"offset": 17, "length": 19}]}, {"rowIndex": 0, "columnIndex": 1, "content": "2", "spans": [{"offset": 46, "length": 1}]}, {"rowIndex": 1, "columnIndex": 0, "content": "Work package title", "spans": [{"offset": 68, "length": 18}]}, {"rowIndex": 1, "columnIndex": 1, "content": "Fusion molecule design, production, and validation", "spans": [{"offset": 96, "length": 50}]}, {"rowIndex": 2, "columnIndex": 0, "columnSpan": 2, "content": "Objectives: 2.1 Design and manufacture immunocytokines. 2.2 Validate molecule activity in-vitro and in-vivo.", "spans": [{"offset": 179, "length": 108}]}, {"rowIndex": 3, "columnIndex": 0, "columnSpan": 2, "content": "Description of work. WP2 focuses on the design, development and production of novel mAb-cytokine fusion molecules and the validation of their pro-inflammatory and antineoplastic activity.\nTask 2.1: Design fusion proteins and cleavage sites. We will develop the optimal structures for the fusion proteins of the top 3\u20135 mAb-cytokine combinations identified in WP1, using advanced techniques in protein design. The design process will include the selection of the most suitable peptide linkers, blocking moieties, TAM-specific cleavage sites and the computational optimization of protein structure and stability.\nTask 2.2: Produce fusion proteins. Building on the designs developed in Task 2.1, we will manufacture the 3\u20135 mAb-cytokine fusion proteins. The protein synthesis will be done by a contract research organization (CRO) selected based on our experience with leading CROs based on quality and punctual production. The production will include the selection of stable molecules with high protein expression and no aggregation.\nTask 2.3: Validate proteins in silico and in vitro. We will confirm the binding via SPR, ELISA, cell-based binding and reporter assays.\nTask 2.4: Validate MiTE\u2019s effects on myeloid, NK, and T cell activity. We will validate MiTEs\u2019 impact on interactions between myeloid and lymphoid cell activity using in-vitro assays of co-cultured huMDMs, NK or T cells. The data from Task 1.1 will be used as control. Cell activity will be measured as in Task 1.1.\nTask 2.5: Validate MiTE activity in NK and T cell killing assays. To assess the efficacy of the fusion proteins in inducing cytotoxic NK and T cell activity, assays of co-cultured huMDMs, NK, or T cells and tumor cells will be treated with the various mAb-cytokine chimeras. The data collected in Task 1.2 will be used as control. NK and T cell activity and cytotoxicity levels will be measured as in Task 1.2.", "spans": [{"offset": 320, "length": 1894}]}], "spans": [{"offset": 0, "length": 2234}]}], "paragraphs": [{"spans": [{"offset": 17, "length": 19}], "content": "Work package number"}, {"spans": [{"offset": 46, "length": 1}], "content": "2"}, {"spans": [{"offset": 68, "length": 18}], "content": "Work package title"}, {"spans": [{"offset": 96, "length": 50}], "content": "Fusion molecule design, production, and validation"}, {"spans": [{"offset": 179, "length": 108}], "content": "Objectives: 2.1 Design and manufacture immunocytokines. 2.2 Validate molecule activity in-vitro and in-vivo."}, {"spans": [{"offset": 320, "length": 187}], "content": "Description of work. WP2 focuses on the design, development and production of novel mAb-cytokine fusion molecules and the validation of their pro-inflammatory and antineoplastic activity."}, {"spans": [{"offset": 508, "length": 422}], "content": "Task 2.1: Design fusion proteins and cleavage sites. We will develop the optimal structures for the fusion proteins of the top 3\u20135 mAb-cytokine combinations identified in WP1, using advanced techniques in protein design. The design process will include the selection of the most suitable peptide linkers, blocking moieties, TAM-specific cleavage sites and the computational optimization of protein structure and stability."}, {"spans": [{"offset": 931, "length": 420}], "content": "Task 2.2: Produce fusion proteins. Building on the designs developed in Task 2.1, we will manufacture the 3\u20135 mAb-cytokine fusion proteins. The protein synthesis will be done by a contract research organization (CRO) selected based on our experience with leading CROs based on quality and punctual production. The production will include the selection of stable molecules with high protein expression and no aggregation."}, {"spans": [{"offset": 1352, "length": 135}], "content": "Task 2.3: Validate proteins in silico and in vitro. We will confirm the binding via SPR, ELISA, cell-based binding and reporter assays."}, {"spans": [{"offset": 1488, "length": 315}], "content": "Task 2.4: Validate MiTE\u2019s effects on myeloid, NK, and T cell activity. We will validate MiTEs\u2019 impact on interactions between myeloid and lymphoid cell activity using in-vitro assays of co-cultured huMDMs, NK or T cells. The data from Task 1.1 will be used as control. Cell activity will be measured as in Task 1.1."}, {"spans": [{"offset": 1804, "length": 410}], "content": "Task 2.5: Validate MiTE activity in NK and T cell killing assays. To assess the efficacy of the fusion proteins in inducing cytotoxic NK and T cell activity, assays of co-cultured huMDMs, NK, or T cells and tumor cells will be treated with the various mAb-cytokine chimeras. The data collected in Task 1.2 will be used as control. NK and T cell activity and cytotoxicity levels will be measured as in Task 1.2."}], "contentFormat": "markdown", "sections": [{"spans": [{"offset": 0, "length": 2234}], "elements": ["/tables/0"]}]}
